        "setup": "1. Sign in to the [Chargebee app](https://app.chargebee.com/login).\n2. Go to **Settings > Configure Chargebee > API Keys and Webhooks > API Keys**.\n3. Click **Add an API Key** and choose **Full-Access Key**.\n4. Copy the key and store it securely. Use the **test site** key for development and the **live site** key for production.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "cb_mcp_api_key": {
        "type": "api_key",
        "label": "Chargebee MCP server API key",
        "generateUrl": "https://app.chargebee.com",
        "setup": "1. Sign in to [Chargebee Billing](https://app.chargebee.com).\n2. Navigate to **Settings > Configure Chargebee > Agentic AI > MCP Servers**.\n3. Open the MCP server you want (for example, **Data Lookup MCP Server**).\n4. In **Access & Authentication**, choose **API Key** and create a key for that MCP server.\n5. Copy the generated key. Clients send it as `Authorization: Bearer YOUR-API-KEY`.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "cb_mcp_oauth": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "Chargebee MCP OAuth access",
        "generateUrl": "https://app.chargebee.com",
        "setup": "1. Sign in to [Chargebee Billing](https://app.chargebee.com).\n2. Navigate to **Settings > Configure Chargebee > Agentic AI > MCP Servers**.\n3. Open the MCP server you want and switch **Access & Authentication** to **OAuth**.\n4. Register/use the OAuth client ID required by your MCP client.\n5. When the client opens Chargebee login, sign in and grant access; the client receives a user-scoped MCP token limited by that user's Chargebee access level.\n\nNote: OAuth is not supported when **Multi-Business Entity** is enabled; use API Key auth instead.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      }
